We use <img/> in HTML to insert images.

Some Atributes of <img/> are :
1. src : Used to specify the location of the image.
2. alt : Specifies alternative text that displays if the image cannot be rendered.
3. height : Determines the height of image.
4. weigth : Determines the width of image.
5. border : specifies thethickness of borders around the image (Defalut = 0 ).

------------------------------------- C O D E -----------------------------------------

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <img src="download.jpeg" alt="Image of a car" height="50" width="50" > 
</body>
</html>

------------------------------------- C O D E -----------------------------------------

In the above example u have to first save your image in the same folder where your HTML file is getting saved.

But what if you want to get the image directly from the internet then the code follows like this :

------------------------------------- C O D E -----------------------------------------

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <img src="https://d27jswm5an3efw.cloudfront.net/app/uploads/2019/07/insert-image-html.jpg" alt="Image of a car" height="50" width="50" > 
</body>
</html>

------------------------------------- C O D E -----------------------------------------

TRY TO RUN THE ABOVE MENTIONED CODE IN YOUR PREFFERED ID :)
